AT|

3. Placing unseen high cards
When an opponent has shown a 3-point range, for example by opening 1NT, assume he has the middle of his range and then subtract points from 40. For example, suppose you hold 11, dummy holds 8 and opener opened 1NT (12-14). 
40-11 = 29
29-8=21
21-13 = 8 for partner +/- 1
Then picture what 8 HCP looks like. E.g., two aces, two kings and a queen, etc. Now begin to place those high cards based on the cards you see and the play. Rehearse this process, until it is second nature. |
